Sacem
SUPPORTS CREATION

   Sacem Cultural Support aims to develop songwriters’ careers, support
   publishers, enhance the value of works and support projects for
   creation and dissemination. Creators who are Sacem members and their
   publishers aim to develop their careers outside France internationally.
   Sacem Cultural Support has chosen to support them.

   To support creation

   To promote live performances

   To facilitate vocational training

   To assist beyond borders

   To support artistic education

Sacem
international Cultural Support

   Promoting songwriters, composers and publishers by:
     * 1. Participating in the vitality of French music and its creators
       for export with their professional and institutional partners;
     * 2. Supporting songwriters and publishers and their professional
       environment for specific projects outside France;
     * 3. Integrating supported projects with Sacem’s wider strategic and
       territorial priorities;

Our support programmes
beyond borders

     * Grants for international festivals - Contemporary classical music
     * Grants for international festivals - Contemporary music and jazz
     * Grants for international tours and concerts - Contemporary
       classical music

     * Grants for international tours and showcases - Contemporary music
       and jazz
     * Grants for professional placements abroad - Music for the moving
       image

   Our programmes

   how to file an application for support ?

BENEFIT
FROM OUR INTERNATIONAL PARTNERSHIPS

   We have developed strong relationships within the French music business
   and with those institutions responsible for exports, as well as with
   major organisations outside France, in order to promote and integrate
   our members internationally.
